# Backend Platform Standards (B1–B14 adapted)

Applies to all work under `web/src/server/` and `web/src/app/api/`.

## Layering (B1)

1. **Routes** (`web/src/app/api/**/route.ts`) — HTTP only: parse, validate, auth gate, call domain/service, map errors.
2. **Domain** (`web/src/server/domain/*.ts`) — business logic and orchestration.
3. **Data** (`web/src/server/data/`, repositories) — persistence only.

Routes MUST NOT query persistence directly. Crossing layers is forbidden.

## Validation (B2)

- Every route validates input with Zod (or shared schema module).
- Every webhook verifies provider signature on **raw body** before JSON parse.
- Services accept typed inputs — no `any`.

## Auth (B3)

- Identity: **Clerk** via `@clerk-nextjs-auth` — not Supabase Auth.
- Use server auth helpers; never trust client-supplied user IDs for authorization.
- Authorization checks belong in domain/services.

## Integrations (B4)

- One client per provider; domain/services orchestrate — routes never import SDKs directly.
- Env vars from `web/src/server/config/runtime.ts` only — **never invent names**.
- Lazy-load `@integration-platform` playbooks per provider.

## Webhooks (B6, B8)

Every webhook route MUST:

1. Read raw body; verify signature; return 400 on failure.
2. Be idempotent by event ID — duplicate delivery must not corrupt state.
3. Respond 2xx quickly; defer heavy work when possible.
4. Log structured context for audit.

## Errors (B7)

- Typed domain errors; routes map to HTTP via shared helper.
- No stack traces or internal paths in client responses.

## Env (B9)

- Required vars validated at boot via runtime config.
- Server secrets MUST NOT use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix.

## Rate limiting (B10)

- Public unauthenticated endpoints use centralized abuse limits from `runtime.ts`.

## Contracts (B14)

- New API surface: delegate `@api-contract-architect` before implementation.
- Align with `DOC/PROJECT PLAN/API and Data/` contracts.

## Phase discipline

- Mid-phase: `ReadLints` + narrow lint/typecheck on touched server files.
- Phase-end: `@backend-quality-enforcer` via `/phase-gate-backend` — not full E2E after every edit.

## Handoffs

| Scope | Owner |
|-------|-------|
| Clerk wiring | `@clerk-nextjs-auth` |
| Backend-only feature | `@senior-backend-devops-developer` |
| Cross-layer feature | `@senior-saas-developer` |
| UI work | `@senior-frontend-specialist` |
